Reasoning: The paper deals with sublinear algorithms for approximating the compressibility of a string with respect to two popular lossless compression schemes, run-length encoding (RLE) and Lempel-Ziv (LZ). This involves studying the combinatorial structure of the string and its substrings, as well as approximating the support size of a distribution. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
